body:
@ssubraveti In `tensorflow`, regularization loss is added to regularization loss key, not the main loss key. 
Unless you use high level API like keras Model or Estimator, all losses have to be collected explicitly. So your total loss would look like:

    loss = main_loss + tf.losses.get_regularization_loss()

@fchollet This is not a `tensorflow` issue, it should be closed.
